-- Chelsea to Play Southend or Brentford in F.A. Cup Fourth Round
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-01-06T15:56:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-06/chelsea-to-play-southend-or-brentford-in-f-a-cup-fourth-round.html
Defending champion Chelsea will play
at Southend or Brentford in the fourth round of English soccer’s
F.A. Cup.  Tottenham will travel to Leeds or Birmingham, while record
11-time winner Manchester United or West Ham will play Fulham or
Blackpool.  Swansea or Arsenal, who drew 2-2 today, will meet Brighton.
Premier League champion  Manchester City  is away to Crystal
Palace or Stoke.  Seven-time winner Chelsea, which won 5-1 at Southampton in
the third round yesterday, beat Liverpool 2-1 in May’s F.A. Cup
final to win the competition for a fourth time in six seasons.
Liverpool plays at Mansfield later today and the winner will
meet Oldham.  Fourth-round draw (with the matches scheduled over the
weekend of Jan. 26/27):  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 